";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:537:"<p>SSL encrypts all data that your website exchanges with visitors. It protects important data such as personal data, login data, credit card information and e-mail addresses. SSL improves user confidence and your search engine ranking. </p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/activate-ssl-for-your-managed-wordpress-websites/">Protecting WordPress with SSL was never easier: Managed WordPress by 1&#038;1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"Philipp Bellmann";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5263:"<img class="aligncenter wp-image-9240 size-full" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ssl-mwp-activate-en.png" alt="SSL WordPress - Activate" width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ssl-mwp-activate-en.png 1280w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ssl-mwp-activate-en-300x169.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ssl-mwp-activate-en-768x432.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ssl-mwp-activate-en-1024x576.png 1024w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ssl-mwp-activate-en-500x281.png 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" />\n<p>SSL encrypts all data that your website exchanges with visitors. It protects important data such as personal data, login data, credit card information and e-mail addresses. SSL improves user confidence and your search engine ranking. 1&amp;1, working together with you, strives to make the Internet a safer place by including powerful SSL encryption with all products.</p>\n<p>Security must be easy to achieve. That is why you can <a href="https://my.1and1.com/AllMyApplications" target="_blank">activate SSL for your Managed WordPress websites conveniently from the 1&amp;1 App Center</a>*:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open the 1&amp;1 App Center.</li>\n<li>In the website detail view, click <strong>Activate SSL</strong>.</li>\n<li>Accept the SSL guidelines to activate SSL for your website.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>We adjust your domain and WordPress settings automatically for SSL. To make sure that your visitors always use an encrypted connection, HTTP traffic will be redirected to HTTPS automatically from now on. The initial setup usually only takes a few seconds and you can continue using your website seamlessly.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-9238 size-full" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/mwp-activate-ssl-app-center.png" alt="WordPress SSL - App Center" width="2796" height="988" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/mwp-activate-ssl-app-center.png 2796w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/mwp-activate-ssl-app-center-300x106.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/mwp-activate-ssl-app-center-768x271.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/mwp-activate-ssl-app-center-1024x362.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2796px) 100vw, 2796px" />\n<p>* This feature is available with all new Web Hosting contracts <strong>and</strong> will be available soon for existing contracts.</p>\n<h2>SSL is included with your Web Hosting contract</h2>\n<p><a href="https://www.1and1.com/ssl-certificates" target="_blank">1&amp;1 SSL Starter</a>: for <strong>blogs</strong> and <strong>personal websites</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Protection for a domain or subdomain</li>\n<li>With a Wildcard Certificate: Protection of an unlimited number of subdomains</li>\n<li>1&amp;1 SSL Starter is a domain validated (DV) SSL certificate.</li>\n<li>DV SSL certificates are perfectly suited to protect projects such as a blog or personal website.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>WordPress SSL at a glance</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>SSL certificates allow encryption of important, confidential data. A requirement for successful e-commerce and social websites.</li>\n<li>Your visitors can easily recognize SSL/HTTPS encryption in their browser.</li>\n<li>SSL encryption increases your website&#8217;s security and creates trust that can turn visitors into customers.</li>\n<li>SSL encryption leads to a better position in the Google hit lists for your website.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Learn more about WordPress, SSL and SEO</h3>\n<div class="column-33">\n<a href="https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-5/"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9132" src="https://community.1und1.de/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/wp-4-5-teaser.png" alt="wordpress 4.5" width="1280" height="720" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-5/">WordPress 4.5 reviewed</a><br />\n</p></div><div class="column-33">\n<a href="https://community.1and1.com/ssl-at-a-glance/"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9113" src="https://community.1und1.de/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/ssl-explained-infographic-seo-teaser-vi.png" alt="ssl-explained-infographic-seo-teaser-vi" width="1280" height="720" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://community.1and1.com/ssl-at-a-glance/">SSL: Protect your website</a><br />\n</p></div><div class="column-33">\n<a href="https://community.1and1.com/guidelines-to-avoid-a-seo-penalty/"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9171" src="https://community.1und1.de/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/seo-guidelines-vi.png" alt="seo-guidelines-vi" width="1280" height="720" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://community.1and1.com/guidelines-to-avoid-a-seo-penalty/">SEO: Guidelines</a><br />\n</p></div><div style="clear: both;"></div></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/activate-ssl-for-your-managed-wordpress-websites/">Protecting WordPress with SSL was never easier: Managed WordPress by 1&#038;1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:82:"https://community.1and1.com/activate-ssl-for-your-managed-wordpress-websites/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"6";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:63:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:46:"Enabling the WordPress Theme and Plugin Editor";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:95:"https://community.1and1.com/enabling-the-wordpress-theme-and-plugin-editor-wordpress-free-mode/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:104:"https://community.1and1.com/enabling-the-wordpress-theme-and-plugin-editor-wordpress-free-mode/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 23 Dec 2016 07:13:13 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:8:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"How-To";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Advanced";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Click & Build";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Expert";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Installation";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"https://community.1and1.com/?p=2433/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:572:"<p>When you use Click&#038;Build to set up your WordPress installation, we set configurations and add functionalities to make it easier and safer for you to build your own website.<br />\nOne of these is disabling the editor in WordPress so you can change one of your themes or plugins.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/enabling-the-wordpress-theme-and-plugin-editor-wordpress-free-mode/">Enabling the WordPress Theme and Plugin Editor</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"Philipp Bellmann";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5056:"<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9141" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/wp-editor-on-vi.png" alt="wp-editor-on-vi" width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/wp-editor-on-vi.png 1280w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/wp-editor-on-vi-300x169.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/wp-editor-on-vi-768x432.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/wp-editor-on-vi-1024x576.png 1024w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/wp-editor-on-vi-500x281.png 500w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" />\n<p>When you use Click&amp;Build to set up your WordPress installation, we set configurations and add functionalities to make it easier and safer for you to build your own website.</p>\n<p>This is why we sometimes limit functionality &#8211; for example, we disable the theme and plugin editors in WordPress for Free Mode installations.</p>\n<h2>Enabling the Theme and Plugin Editors in wp-config.php</h2>\n<p>If you use a 1&amp;1 WordPress default installation, you can enable the editors by changing your wp-config.php file. From here it&#8217;s a few steps to enable the editors again:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Use SFTP and go to the location of your WordPress site. <a href="http://help.1and1.com/hosting-c37630/webspace-and-access-c85098/ftp-c37631/connect-to-your-webspace-via-sftp-using-filezilla-a683348.html" target="_blank">Learn how</a></li>\n<li>Open <strong>wp-config.php</strong> on your computer.</li>\n<li>Search for:\n<pre> define(''DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT'', <span style="color: #00ccff;">true</span>);</pre>\n</li>\n<li>Change true to false:\n<pre> define(''DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT'', <span style="color: #cc99ff;">false</span>);</pre>\n</li>\n<li>Save the file and upload it back again.</li>\n</ol>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The theme editor is now available in the <strong>Appearance</strong> tab:</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-4747" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/wordpress-theme-editor-active.png" alt="wordpress-theme-editor-active" width="1344" height="709" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/wordpress-theme-editor-active.png 1344w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/wordpress-theme-editor-active-300x158.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/wordpress-theme-editor-active-1024x540.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1344px) 100vw, 1344px" />\n<h2>Security Risks When Enabling the Editors<strong><br />\n</strong></h2>\n<p><img class="alignright wp-image-4772" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/security-vi2-crop-225x300.png" alt="security-vi2-crop" width="113" height="150" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/security-vi2-crop-225x300.png 225w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/security-vi2-crop.png 354w" sizes="(max-width: 113px) 100vw, 113px" />The first risk is that someone could have gained admin access to your site. When that happens and you have your editor enabled, they could use that to add any code they want. At that point they don’t need SFTP access or anything like that, WordPress already provides all the access they need to modify your site and misuse it.</p>\n<h2>Theme or Plugin Updates Might Break Changes Made Using the Editors<strong><br />\n</strong></h2>\n<p>The second risk is that it makes it really easy to change something in a way that most likely will break when there is an update for that theme or plugin.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>In most cases it’s the theme you want to adjust and there are multiple ways in doing that. If it’s only CSS then you should use a plugin (for example: <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/simple-custom-css/" target="_blank">Simple Custom CSS</a>) that has a CSS editor which allows you to change the styling independently of the theme. So when the theme gets updated or you switch themes, your custom CSS is still loaded.</li>\n<li>Another way is to build a Child theme. This is a more advanced way of overwriting parts of a theme which is not always that easy. But when you understand how it works, you can do great things with it.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Learn more about <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Child_Themes">Child Themes</a> (WordPress Codex).</p>\n<p><em><strong>Note</strong>: This Post was initially published by Marko Heijnen on January 22, 2015.</em></p>\n<h3>You might also like:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a title="Getting Started with WordPress" href="https://community.1and1.com/getting-started-with-wordpress-2015/">Getting started with WordPress<br />\n</a>This is how you get started with your new website: basics, content, themes, security and more.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/enabling-the-wordpress-theme-and-plugin-editor-wordpress-free-mode/">Enabling the WordPress Theme and Plugin Editor</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:100:"https://community.1and1.com/enabling-the-wordpress-theme-and-plugin-editor-wordpress-free-mode/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"11";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}