 emphasizes inner beauty – the improvements are found on the inside. Some things, however, are simpler and prettier in the process.</p>\n<p>As always, <strong>Managed WordPress websites will be updated by 1&amp;1 automatically.</strong> If you have installed WordPress yourself or use a standard installation from the 1&amp;1 App Center, you can update to 4.6 from your WordPress <strong>Dashboard.</strong><strong> </strong>Select<strong> </strong><strong>Updates</strong> and click <strong>Update Now</strong>.</p>\n<a href="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/WordPress-4-6-whats-new.jpg"><img class="size-large wp-image-9470 aligncenter" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/WordPress-4-6-whats-new-1024x576.jpg" alt="WordPress-4-6-whats-new" width="1024" height="576" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/WordPress-4-6-whats-new-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/WordPress-4-6-whats-new-300x169.jpg 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/WordPress-4-6-whats-new-768x432.jpg 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/WordPress-4-6-whats-new-500x281.jpg 500w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/WordPress-4-6-whats-new.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a>\n<h2>Improvements to the Editor</h2>\n<p>The Editor has received two interesting updates:</p>\n<h3>Broken Link Checker</h3>\n<p>Links are now checked directly during input. If a link does not work, an error message is displayed.</p>\n<h3><img class="aligncenter wp-image-9477 size-full" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-4-6-broken-link-checker-e1472454735357.png" alt="wp-4-6-broken-link-checker" width="774" height="696" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-4-6-broken-link-checker-e1472454735357.png 774w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-4-6-broken-link-checker-e1472454735357-300x270.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-4-6-broken-link-checker-e1472454735357-768x691.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 774px) 100vw, 774px" />Easy restore</h3>\n<p>WordPress saves automatically while you are writing. In the case of a malfunction, such as a browser crash, your content will be restored automatically and you can continue your work without interruption.</p>\n<h2>Support for installed fonts</h2>\n<p>The admin screen now automatically uses fonts installed on your system. For instance San Francisco (Mac), Segoe UI (Windows) or Roboto (Android).</p>\n<p>The goal is to reduce loading times in the admin area and make it look more like a native, local application.</p>\n<h2>Shiny Updates</h2>\n<p>So-called <em>Shiny Updates</em> will replace the old update process in WordPress 4.6. Updates, installation and deleting plugins and themes now no longer redirect to a new site, but happen directly <em>in place</em>.</p>\n<h2>Inner beauty</h2>\n<p>There are several noteworthy improvements under the hood:</p>\n<h3>Speed improvements</h3>\n<p>Slow site buildup can lead to losing visitors. To improve response times and shorten loading times, WordPress can now execute certain processes in the background. Resource hints allow pre-fetching and rendering of certain websites, DNS lookups and connection handshakes in the background &#8211; i.e. even before a visitor clicks on a link.</p>\n<h3>Improved support for HTTP standards</h3>\n<p>The HTTP API now uses the requests library. This allows support of parallel HTTP requests, case-insensitive headers and internationalized domains.</p>\n<h3>Flexible and intuitive queries</h3>\n<p>The query term is now complemented by the WP_Term query and the new WP_Post_Type object will make working with post-types easier and more predictable.</p>\n<h3>Updated JavaScript libraries</h3>\n<p>WordPress 4.6 contains Masonry 3.3.2, imagesLoaded 3.2.0, MediaElement.js 2.22.0, TinyMCE 4.4.1 and Backbone.js 1.3.3.</p>\n<h3>Faster multi-sites</h3>\n<p>Multi-sites are made faster through improved caching of queries. WP_Site_Query and WP_Network_Query now make it easier for developers to create reliable queries.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-6/">WordPress 4.6: What&#8217;s new?</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-6/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:63:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"How to transfer your domain to 1&amp;1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://community.1and1.com/how-to-transfer-your-domain-to-1and1/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"https://community.1and1.com/how-to-transfer-your-domain-to-1and1/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 21 Jul 2016 08:23:38 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:8:{i:0;a: